# =============================================================================
# Beach, Please environment
# Copy this to .env (in the backend/ directory) and pick ONE provider profile.
# Every profile is OpenAI-compatible. The agent code itself never changes.
# =============================================================================

# ---- Profile A: OpenAI (default) --------------------------------------------
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-replace-me
OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ---- Profile B: LM Studio (local) -------------------------------------------
# 1. Install LM Studio.
# 2. Download a tool-capable model. Confirmed working with this app:
#      - qwen3.5-4b           (fast, ~25s per turn on M-series Mac)
#      - qwen2.5-7b-instruct  (recommended sweet spot)
#      - llama-3.1-8b-instruct
#    Avoid gpt-oss-* models in LM Studio for now \u2014 they emit raw
#    template tokens via the OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
# 3. In LM Studio, start the local server on port 1234 and load the model.
# 4. Comment out Profile A above and uncomment these:
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=lm-studio
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# OPENAI_MODEL=qwen3.5-4b

# ---- Profile C: Ollama (local) ----------------------------------------------
# 1. brew install ollama && ollama serve
# 2. ollama pull llama3.1:8b   (or qwen2.5:7b)
# 3. Comment out Profile A above and uncomment these:
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=ollama
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# OPENAI_MODEL=llama3.1

# ---- Optional tuning --------------------------------------------------------
# CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=600
# REQUEST_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=20
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
